o pull out of NATO not only would be a fundamental change in our foreign po=
licy, but it would raise the question you=E2=80=99re asking, and it would g=
et to the Supreme Court I think for the first time: Can presidents break tr=
eaties on their own?=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Trump will do this in the environmental area, too. He=E2=80=99s going to re=
-pull us out of the Paris Accords, which he
tried to pull us out of before. I think we=E2=80=99re going to pull out of =
a series of global warming and environmental agreements, too, which will ra=
ise questions.

=E2=80=A6But Can He?
--------------

What are people going to expect on Day One? Is it going to
feel like there are a bunch of eruptions because of Trump=E2=80=99s executi=
ve orders, or is it just going to be shock-and-awe psychological warfare?

=C2=A0

The areas where you=E2=80=99re going to see Trump have more success are goi=
ng to be pure foreign policy areas. So if Trump wants to drop a bomb on Teh=
ran, if Trump wants to start intervening in Ukraine and trying to produce a=
 peace agreement, those are areas where
the courts have generally let presidents have a free hand. The president=E2=
=80=99s power of foreign affairs, national security, intelligence, espionag=
e, surveillance=E2=80=94those are all areas where the courts have not reall=
y gotten in the president=E2=80=99s way. In other areas, like finding illeg=
al aliens and removing them, you=E2=80=99re going to see the courts get inv=
olved. But outside of our borders, that=E2=80=99s where you=E2=80=99re goin=
g to see the biggest changes immediately on Day One. If Trump were to say, =
=E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re withdrawing from
NATO,=E2=80=9D that would be earth-shattering for foreign policy, but he wo=
uld be able to do it.

=C2=A0

I want to go through some of the executive orders Trump has proposed and fo=
r you to let me know if you think they=E2=80=99re toothless or if they have=
 any chance of survival, starting with ending birthright citizenship=E2=80=
=A6

=C2=A0

Immediately
going to court. He=E2=80=99s pushing a big rock up a steep hill on that one=
=2E I think he=E2=80=99s going to lose.

=C2=A0

He wants to pull us out of the Paris Climate Agreement. Can he do that?

=C2=A0

Obama and Biden made that easier because they=E2=80=99re not even treaties.=
 They=E2=80=99ve never been submitted to the Senate for ratification, so
they=E2=80=99re just promises by the United States. So yes, Trump can termi=
nate that on Day One.

=C2=A0

Can he impose tariffs on Mexico on Day One?

=C2=A0

Yes, it=E2=80=99s possible because Congress has actually given the presiden=
t the power to impose retaliatory tariffs on other countries in response to=
 unfair trade practices.

=C2=A0

On Day One, can he pardon everyone who took part in the January 6th insurre=
ction?

=C2=A0

Unfortunately, yes. The pardon power only has two exceptions: You can only =
pardon people for federal crimes, and you can=E2=80=99t pardon people for i=
mpeachment. He can even pardon people who haven=E2=80=99t been convicted ye=
t.

=C2=A0

Do you think everyday people are going to feel the impact of the Trump pres=
idency on Day One?

=C2=A0

Yes. And I think the area they=E2=80=99re going to see it is with tariffs, =
because prices are going to go up. And immigration, because I think you=E2=
=80=99re going to see an effort to remove illegal aliens, many of whom are =
part of our
communities=E2=80=94I think that=E2=80=99s going to disrupt a lot of the to=
wns where we live. =C2=A0

