ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>You=E2=80=99ve previously called for Tr=
ump=E2=80=99s impeachment, so why do
you think that Trump needs to now expand his executive power?</strong></p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;marg=
in-bottom:0px;">I don=E2=80=99t know if he needs to expand it, but I think =
he should use it to the greatest extent that we have allowed past president=
s to use it. I think a lot of the challenges our country is facing are goin=
g to be rooted in national security and foreign affairs, and that=E2=80=99s=
 where our Constitution does shift a lot of the power to the
president. I think, given the pressures on the country, we=E2=80=99re going=
 to see a more energetic executive because our system demands it.</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;"><strong>How can Trump expand his powers?</strong></p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:=
0px;">He=E2=80=99s going to start issuing executive orders. The early flash=
point is going to be immigration. He=E2=80=99s going to try to continue bui=
lding
the border wall. He=E2=80=99s going to have to find money for it in existin=
g accounts, and he=E2=80=99s going to try to expand enforcement of the immi=
gration laws. I assume he=E2=80=99s going to try to reverse the priorities =
that the Biden administration had in effect.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin=
-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">But I think the biggest figh=
t in the courts and in public will be figuring out how to get the states an=
d cities to cooperate. That=E2=80=99s an area where Congress and the Consti=
tution have
given the president a lot of power to enforce immigration laws. If Trump ta=
kes the more cautious route that=E2=80=99s more within our norms, I think h=
e=E2=80=99s going to cut off funding to the cities and states that don=E2=
=80=99t cooperate.=C2=A0</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table align=3D"center" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cells=
