strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The areas where you=E2=80=99re going to see Tru=
mp have more success are going to be pure foreign policy areas. So if Trump=
 wants to drop a bomb on Tehran, if Trump wants to start intervening in Ukr=
aine and trying to produce a peace agreement, those are areas where
the courts have generally let presidents have a free hand. The president=E2=
=80=99s power of foreign affairs, national security, intelligence, espionag=
e, surveillance=E2=80=94those are all areas where the courts have not reall=
y gotten in the president=E2=80=99s way. In other areas, like finding illeg=
al aliens and removing them, you=E2=80=99re going to see the courts get inv=
olved. But outside of our borders, that=E2=80=99s where you=E2=80=99re goin=
g to see the biggest changes immediately on Day One. If Trump were to say, =
=E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re withdrawing from
NATO,=E2=80=9D that would be earth-shattering for foreign policy, but he wo=
uld be able to do it.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>I want to go through some=
 of the executive orders Trump has proposed and for you to let me know if y=
ou think they=E2=80=99re toothless or if they have any chance of survival, =
starting with ending birthright citizenship=E2=80=A6</strong></p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">Immediately
going to court. He=E2=80=99s pushing a big rock up a steep hill on that one=
=2E I think he=E2=80=99s going to lose.</=
p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom=
:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>He wants =
