gin-bottom:0px;">Obama and Biden made that easier because they=E2=80=99re n=
ot even treaties. They=E2=80=99ve never been submitted to the Senate for ra=
tification, so
they=E2=80=99re just promises by the United States. So yes, Trump can termi=
nate that on Day One.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Can he impose tariffs on =
Mexico on Day One?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Yes, it=E2=80=99s possible =
because Congress has actually given the president the power to impose retal=
iatory tariffs on other countries in response to unfair trade practices.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;mar=
gin-bottom:0px;"><strong>On Day One, can he pardon everyone who took part i=
n the January 6th insurrection?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bot=
tom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Unfortunately,=
 yes. The pardon power only has two exceptions: You can only pardon people =
for federal crimes, and you can=E2=80=99t pardon people for impeachment. He=
 can even pardon people who haven=E2=80=99t been convicted yet.</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;"><strong>Do you think everyday people are going to feel the impact =
of the Trump presidency on Day One?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin=
-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Yes. And I think the area th=
ey=E2=80=99re going to see it is with tariffs, because prices are going to =
go up. And immigration, because I think you=E2=80=99re going to see an effo=
rt to remove illegal aliens, many of whom are part of our
communities=E2=80=94I think that=E2=80=99s going to disrupt a lot of the to=
wns where we live. <strong>=C2=A0</strong></p></div>
